text:
:flag-et: 3 days ago I started *sneezing* and I was *coughing* here and then. By the second day, I was having a hard time *swallowing* anything! *My throat hurts!* 

It was *so hard not to panic,* My monkey mind was stronger than ever!

The 3rd day I used some *_arena_ /አረግሬሳ/* and it looks like I was just panicking from a regular *Pneumonia (ምች)* + a regular *Flu.* Which I have recovered right now *thank God.*

*I believe there are cases like mine which leads to Panicking! Unnecessary phone calls to emergency medical services! Or easily consume false info!* 

So why not build an *online test* that reduces unnecessary emergency traffics and panics? With all current projects going on am confident enough to say we can develop & launch *the simplest Online test* with algorithms that either shows a result _*"You should see a doctor"*_ or _*"Your symptoms are regular"*_ 

_*with methods to cure the problem or further actions suggested if they aren't cured.*_ 
  (Then this data with geolocation in Ethiopia will help us to analyze which areas are highly showing the Covid 19 - *Real symptoms if they ever occur)*  

I build websites for a living *(Am In Gondar, Ethiopia)* but I feel like being a lot better with *UI/UX designing,* So if you believe this could help out *on the side with ongoing projects,* reply and let's do this within *2-3 days!* am willing to put in *every hr on this!*  

Surely we will need *ad campaigns* for people to *run the tests*, People with *Adobe suit, Ui Ux designers* and with *Copywriters* may be *videographers too* for higher quality content, this should be making a huge impact.
Mainly satisfying the term _*"Speed over Perfection"  (I know that there are self-test sites that are helping a lot)*_
_What do you think?_

_On top of all Egziabher Yeker Yebeln! Yemarn._

_<@U0107JERE9L>_ _<@UV8B0679P>_ _<@U0106M26108>_

text: ...... Even seemingly costless social distancing is hard to implement. Our lifestyle is deeply communal, with extended families traditionally sharing the burdens and bounties of life together, eating meals from the same plate. Our traditional and rain-dependent agriculture is dictated by the fixed timeframes of weather cycles in which planting, weeding and harvesting must happen. The slightest disruption to that chain, even for a brief period, can spell disaster, further jeopardising already tenuous food supply and food security.  PM Dr. Abiy  Thus this is a sensitive area we should see before the problems deepen ..... Source : <https://www.ft.com/content/c12a09c8-6db6-11ea-89df-41bea055720b?shareType=nongift>
